                                                                                                                                    Great Offshore in buy mode

     OUR CORRESPONDENT
               
	Mumbai, Jan. 15: Great Offshore Ltd will buy a controlling stake in an overseas rig manufacturing company for close to $1.4 billion. 
    
	In a notice to the Bombay Stock Exchange, Great Offshore said, The company has made an offer to purchase a controlling stake in an overseas company.
    
	The said offer has been accepted by the board of the overseas company and subsequently by the board of Great Offshore.
    
	Though the company did not divulge the name of the company, sources said Great Offshore is targeting a rig manufacturer in the UK.
    
	Speaking to The Telegraph, Great Offshore MD Vijay Kanthilal Sheth said, We are still in the due diligence stage and, as a result, will not be able to disclose the name of the overseas company.
    
	The company builds harsh environment, semi-submersible, sixth generation drilling rigs. With this acquisition, Great Offshore will own two such drilling rigs. 
    
	The transaction is subject to the satisfactory completion of due diligence, execution of definitive documents and undertakings and receipt of all necessary approvals as may be required in India and abroad, it said.
    
	The Great Offshore scrip closed 1.28 per cent up at Rs 1093.50 on the Bombay Stock Exchange today.
    
	The company had stated that they will look at inorganic growth. This acquisition is a clear pointer to the same, said an industry analyst.
    
	During the second quarter of the current financial year, the companys income from operations grew 20 per cent to Rs 152.33 crore from Rs 127.05 crore in the year-ago period. 
                                                                
